About 4,000 Turkish citizens are
stranded in  Libya , sheltering in a hanger near the city of
Benghazi, Hurriyet newspaper reported.  Turkish companies had taken their employees to Benghazi,
aiming to evacuate them, the newspaper said. The unrest against
Libyan leader  Muammar Qaddafi  shut transport at the cityâ€™s
airport and port, it said.  There are 28 Turkish companies active in Libya with $3
billion in contracts, Hurriyet said. Fourteen have suffered
